      },
      "date": "2013-01-31 23:26:54.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 11: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(11 inline comments)\n\nIn order to avoid LU-2730, the LMV should return an error like -EOPNOTSUPP to the caller for calling \"lfs rm_entry\" if there is only a single MDT.  This will avoid the 2.4 client from crashing the MDS with REINT_RMENTRY until it is patched.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 11
    },
    {
      "id": "9cf6f6d62f2e25b0d0accecea6baedcc1b2cebba",
