        "email": "di.wang@intel.com",
        "username": "wangdi",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-02-01 00:55:02.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 11:\n\nSo you mean we should add single MDT check in lmv_unlink temporarily? and remove it later when server patch is landed?\n \nAnyway, I think one use case to use rm_entry is that  if one MDT(non0)  failed and can not get back. the administrator should be able to clear those broken remote entry with the command, so even there is one MDT, this command should still be allowed.  \n\nBut communicating with old server is different story.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 11
    },
