        "_account_id": 12,
        "name": "wangdi",
        "email": "di.wang@intel.com",
        "username": "wangdi",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-02-01 19:59:37.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 13: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nThis patch conflict with this one\n\ncommit 92c24af6c7c9d0836bf866975bc0a1d641a4a815\nAuthor: Sergii Glushchenko <sergii_glushchenko@xyratex.com>\nDate:   Tue Jan 29 16:19:40 2013 +0200\n\n    LU-1431 ptlrpc: PTLRPC_BRW_MAX_SIZE usage cleanup.\n    \n    Clean-up the layering in current code by eliminating direct\n    usage of PTLRPC_BRW_MAX_SIZE macro outside of the ptlrpc\n    module. This should help us acheive \"floating\" max brw size\n    value across the cluster, which in turn should help with\n    4MB IO task.\n    \nNeed to rebase the patch.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 13
    },
    {
      "id": "e0b085ab9fca7699b0000059582fe46fa977e2a5",
      "author": {
